				<td colspan="2"><span>Edit: Myself I think it is very worth having the group message on the hotkey simply for the fact that most of the times you will use FM they will not be in range of any message that may come up in the blue text, and that is even if they have bard messages on (and there is very few people who do). I have never yet had anyone complain that my message is broadcast to the group as it lets them know whats going on. As far as mez goes you positivly need a message on that otherwise you will find people trying to offtank or tank 2 mobs at a time as they didn't know you were trying to mez it...
<br />

<br />

<br />
my key is..
<br />

<br />
/attack off
<br />
/stopsong
<br />
/alt activate 212
<br />
/gsay I HAVE USED FADING MEMORIES...DO NOT ASSIST
<br />

<br />
As for what to do now it depends on what style you are playing...if you find yourself doing alot of pulling it may be worth investing the time in the bellow aa. I didn't do that straight away myself to be honest but I did do it at level 64 as a friend kept bugging me to get it (monk lol) and I regret not having done it straight away. Awesome aa for pulling. I havn't yet gotten any of the upgrades (only 60 aa atm) and for practical purposes I don't think I will until I have aa to waste. I am never fighting anything the stun could be used on really so it serves its purpose as a tagging pulling tool fine as it is...
<br />

<br />
Just depends what you do most really...</span></td>
