				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: finaly have fade now what?<a name="70974"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 13 04 2:14 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I put my FADE hotkey on my main hotkey page as well.  If I had to change hotkey pages I would probably mess it up, but thats just me.
<br />

<br />
I use a simple group message. 
<br />

<br />
/g *** fading aggro ***
<br />

<br />
I think this is a good idea because it allows you to communicate with your group automatically.  Its a simple 1 liner.  I dont even use caps.  They can easily ignore it if they want.  To me its important for group members to communicate unless they know each other well.  
<br />

<br />
I get in a lot of pick-up groups so typically I'm with people I don't very well.  Even the smallest amount of communication can go a long way.  It lets them know a little bit about whats going on.  As a puller (and a slow typist) I dont have time to explain.  When they see that I've faded during a pull they instantly know I'm still working on it or that something may have gone wrong.
<br />

<br />
I personally like it when people use simple group messages.  I hate long messages, multi-line messages, and messages that are spammed out too much.  Fade is not frequent enough to qualify as spam IMO.
<br />

<br />
--
<br />
Dumaine</span></td>
