				<td colspan="2"><span>actually ...invis doesnt break when you run into a see invis mob unless the mob hits you.
<br />

<br />
this is actually very nice for pulling a see invis mob around non- see invis mobs that aren't social (of course plain old invis works the same way).  Proximity pull the see invis mob and run him to group...just make sure you aren't cast on or hit and you can drag a mob across a hostile zone single.  
<br />

<br />
