				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: finaly have fade now what?<a name="71298"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 20 04 1:07 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I use the function keys to cast songs (F1 = song 1, etc.) and then have room in my hotkey bank for Fade, Deftdance, clickies, Raid messages (HoS, Slow, etc), my assist key, etc.
<br />

<br />
Do what works for you.  I used to keep Deftdance on page 2 and I had no problem pressing Shift+2 in time to save my arse.  I also mapped song 1 on page 2 so it will switch me back to my main hotkey page when I click it.  So what I used to do was set up a pulling bank on Page 2 with PoV in slot 1.  Once I had the mob on its way, I'd hit PoV to being my group twist and it would automatically move me back to my main hotkey bank.
<br />

<br />
Play around with your key mappings under Options.  You can do a lot of useful things that way.</span></td>
